  "prompt": "Why can't I change my profile picture on Quora via my phone?",
  "response": "If you're having trouble changing your profile picture on Quora via your phone, there could be several reasons behind it. Here are a few common issues and solutions:\n\n1. **App Version**: Ensure that you are using the latest version of the Quora app. Sometimes, outdated versions may have bugs or limitations.\n\n2. **App Permissions**: Check if the Quora app has the necessary permissions to access your phone\u2019s storage or camera. You can manage app permissions through your phone\u2019s settings.\n\n3. **Internet Connection**: Make sure you have a stable internet connection. A weak or intermittent connection might prevent updates from being saved.\n\n4. **App Cache**: Clearing the app cache can sometimes resolve issues. Go to your phone\u2019s settings, find the Quora app, and clear the cache.\n\n5. **Platform Issues**: Occasionally, there might be issues on Quora\u2019s side. Check their support forums or reach out to their customer service for assistance.\n\n6. **Account Restrictions**: Ensure that your account is in good standing. Sometimes, accounts might have restrictions preventing certain actions.\n\n7. **Technical Glitches**: Try uninstalling and reinstalling the app. This can resolve a lot of technical issues.\n\nIf you\u2019ve tried these steps and are still facing issues, it might be helpful to contact Quora support for further assistance.",
